item.title: Hello world...Summer Camp is almost here!
item.dc:creator: richard
item.content:encoded: Welcome to our Summer Camp 2016: 30th July - 6th August. This year FreeSpirit ESU have teamed up with 1st Griffithstown Scouts. Griff Scouts have been one of our main feeder groups for many years and we are looking forward to an excelent joint camp with them. Please come back to these pages regularly during the camp to follow the "exploits" of your sons and daughters. The leaders and Explorers will be updating these pages every day with comments and photos. Please also use the "comment" feature on this page...we have a prize for the most comments from a parent! You may also want to review the main BrumJam site, it can be found here: http://www.brumjam.org/

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: richard
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: And we're off!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The intrepid Scouts and Explorers all met up at Oasis car park at 11.15...the trailer was packed...and we're off for BrumJam!

item.title: Ruling the school!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The intrepid FreeSpirits and their good friends from Griffithstown Scouts travelled the length of the country... And arrived in Birmingham. A very busy afternoon putting up our tents..a fantastic tea of chicken fajita wraps....and then we headed off to the Opening Ceremony... Everyone with a Welsh flag. We have arrived!

item.title: First Impressions
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The sun was setting as we made our way around the entire jamboree site in one long profession. We ended up in the main arena where the Opening Ceremony kicked off...a simple affair, but good fun. The evening finished with most of the unit gathering in our main mess Tent for hot chocolate and biscuits.

item.title: Water Actvities...and a Bullpit
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: We were up bright and early today in order to grab the coach to the nearby lake. We will be there all day sailing, canoeing etc. While we were waiting for the bus, the main man popped over to chill with us - UK Chief Commissioner Wayne Bulpitt.

item.title: A canoe...and a sinking!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: A great day on the water. The morning was spent in open canoes...races, a game of polo and a massive water fight! The morning was finished with a sinking, or two!! After lunch it was windsurfing all the way... Photos to follow. Asia Bollywood dancing for us tonight!

item.title: A cool gateway!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The early evening was spent making the coolest gateway.

item.title: Team Lard!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The combined forces from FreeSpirits and Griffithstown Scouts - "Free Griff" - or Team Lard, we're hard at work cooking a healthy, low calorie breakfast... Sausages, bacon, eggy bread, beans...and cajun garlic mushrooms... Mmm

item.title: Culture and a poo!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today has been spent on site - world issues, culture, rhythm and dance. Imagine the scene... Our intrepid Free Griff boys and girls doing the moves to Saturday Night Fever, and Zorba's theme! Photos/videos to follow. We followed this by learning Chinese fan dancing. And this is our favourite site wagon!

item.title: Further culture....the Turban Twins
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The final part of our culture experience... I don't believe Asia will be the same again!

item.title: Climbing and Archery
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: We awoke to steady drizzle... But, fortified with another awesome breakfast from Team Lard - bacon and pancakes, and we headed over to the activity zone for some climbing followed by some Archery.

item.title: Tree Top Challenge & a ladder!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our afternoon saw the unit split into different groups continuing with various adventurous activities... A Tree Top assault course, followed by climbing a massive ladder.

item.title: Alton Towers...What a day!!!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded:
Up very early today (6am), breakfasted...and now currently sitting on a coach heading for Roller-coaster heaven!

500 Scouts arrived at Alton Towers with the aim of achieving speed, screams and a great day...roller coaster heaven delivered! Galatica, 13, Rita, Nemesis and The Run-away Train were ticked off by lunch time. White Water Rapids, Oblivion and Smiler after lunch...Smiler, OMG! Brilliant!! Many more photos to come...when better Wifi allows.

item.title: Conga and a neon beach party
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Our great day was not over...following a tea of meatballs and pasta, it was time to get into party kit. Welsh flag dresses, onsies, kilts, Welsh afro wigs, dragon suits....and lots of Neon face paint. The conga then started from our pitch, throughout the entire camp to the main arena... The happening unit had arrived and the cheasy party dancing could start.

item.title: It's a Knockout
item.dc:creator: buff

item.title: Tingle and Lube!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Thursday evening saw successful "manoeuvres" by Team Lube and Team Tingle...if you are in the know, then you understand what we mean!

item.title: Pool party, a segway roll and a "small" jump!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Friday - our last full day of activities and the sun was shinning....so we grabbed our swim kit and headed off to the swimming pool for the "pool party". Here we played frisbee, pool rugby and pool rounders and then enjoyed a free slush drink! From the pool we headed off to the activity field for "extreme craft! various knotting challenges, origami, power knitting, chocolate and fritters! After lunch we headed into the woods for Bushcraft - fire starting, shelter building and an interesting challenge involving purifying water in the field without man-made filters. The bar was then raised with segway racing...Buff managed to "completely roll" a segway, Ella seemed to ride her own course, but all agreed it was a great activity. Zorb wars was a battle of strength and stamina with all of us enjoying bouncing off each other, the floor and the course and an activity in which Jack excelled! ...and then the finale of the week. The big jump from many meters high, into a massive "paper bag".

item.title: The Closing Ceremony, cheese...and home
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Friday evening saw us all wearing red - Welsh tops, Welsh onsie's, dragon suits - and heading off in the sub-camp parade towards the main arena for the closing ceremony. Our week was coming to a close - a great venue, a well organised jamboree, we made some new friends (1st Eye), we bumped into some old friends (Sue, Jo, Stuart)...and I am sure that we will be back. The closing ceremony saw the Camp Chief and the County Commissioner officially close the camp before the live music began....and here's Bronwin! The evening ended with a tradition at FreeSpirit - a serious "cheese" party. Many cheeses, a choice of regular biscuits, chocolate digestives, jaffa biscuits...and a first, chocolate waffles! Our new friends from 1st Eye joined us until lights out around midnight. Saturday saw us drop the camp, pack everything into our van and trailer...and head for home. A fantastic camp...many thanks to all that attended. See you in September.
